  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether the participants have improved their scores
      on health related quality of life (HRQL) 1 year after completing a learning and mastery
      course and whether sociodemographic variables are associated with HRQL.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Persons with chronic illnesses have to adjust to changes in their life-style. In the last 10
      years Learning and Mastery Centres have been established in Norwegian hospitals to offer
      patient education for the chronically ill. It is not known whether these courses impact any
      changes in HRQL 1 year after course completion.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
